article.headline: Oral Roberts 86, SMS 76
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 33 points to lead Oral Roberts to an 86-76 win over Southwest Missouri State on Saturday as part of the ESPN Bracket Buster competition. Oral Roberts (21-5), representing the Mid-Continent Conference, watched its 10-point lead midway through the second half evaporate to 64-62 with 7:49 left before rallying to lead 75-64 with 4:23 left. Southwest Missouri (14-10), from the Missouri Valley, trailed by as many as 11 in the first half but rallied early in the second half to trim a 49-40 halftime deficit to 54-50 with 15:25 to go. Oral Roberts went on the 10-4 run to lead 64-54 with 10:50 left. Southwest Missouri responded with a 8-0 run to get to within 64-62. Green scored six of the next 11 points for the Golden Eagles as they took a 75-64 lead. Larry Owens scored 12 for Oral Roberts and Luke Spencer-Gardner and Jonathan Bluitt each had 11. Tamarr Maclin had 24 points and 19 rebounds for Southwest Missouri and Anthony Shavies had 14.
